95
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:10,852
I see. Well, then...

96
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:12,938
THE OCEAN, US, AND BLUE

97
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:14,105
Hey, Iori.

98
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:19,236
Were you excited when you started college life?

99
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,739
-Huh?
-How did you feel?

100
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:26,326
Now that you mention it, I did...

101
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:28,828
feel excited...

102
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:31,498
Then I'm sure

103
00:05:32,624 --> 00:05:34,251
you'll have fun.

104
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:38,922
Iori will team up with me for practice.

105
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:41,383
Then I'll practice with Kohei.

106
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:43,718
This is really simple.

107
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:46,388
You'll simulate what it's like
to breathe underwater.

108
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,139
Okay...

109
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,767
Put the regulator in your mouth and breathe in.

110
00:05:51,393 --> 00:05:52,394
Okay.

111
00:05:57,732 --> 00:05:58,733
How was it?

112
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,362
It feels really different from breathing normally.

113
00:06:02,571 --> 00:06:05,907
Correct. It's as if the air flows in
all at once when you breathe in.

114
00:06:06,157 --> 00:06:07,659
That's true.

115
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:10,620
You have to use force to breathe in.

116
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:15,041
Yeah. You might have a hard time
breathing until you get used to it.

117
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:18,169
-Okay.
-Let's try actually diving underwater.

118
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:21,047
Okay...

119
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,224
Iori...

120
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,649
Hey, Iori.

121
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,109
What?

122
00:06:41,276 --> 00:06:42,819
Why are you out of breath?

123
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:44,487
Because I can't breathe.

124
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,948
Then why are you carrying
that tank on your back?

125
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:51,453
I'm scared of breathing underwater.

126
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,496
-Scared?
-Yes.

127
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:58,460
I see. Well, you might feel confused at first,
but you'll get used to it.

128
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:02,631
Then I'll try it one more time.

129
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,391
What's wrong? Are you okay?

130
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:14,976
Water leaked into my mask...

131
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,479
Maybe it's too loose. Let me see.

132
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,315
Thank you very much!

133
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:23,109
-Who are those customers?
-Wait up!

134
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:26,363
Oh. They came to dive before their business trip.

135
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:28,740
That looks rough.

136
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:32,077
They look really busy,
but they even brought their suits.

137
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:35,121
-It's reassuring, right?
-Reassuring?

138
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:36,706
It's true, right?

139
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:40,752
They're spending their
precious money and time on diving.

140
00:07:40,919 --> 00:07:41,920
In other words...

141
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:46,216
it proves just how alluring this place is!

142
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:53,640
You said it's scary underwater, right?

143
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:56,267
-Sorry.
-You don't have to apologize.

144
00:07:56,976 --> 00:08:01,272
Even I get scared when I think about what would happen
if I run out of air.

145
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:03,775
Do you know what this is?

146
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:06,444
-Uh...
-This is called an octopus.

147
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:08,405
It's a spare regulator.

148
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:12,033
You give it to your buddy if they run out of air.

149
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,036
And the weight belt always faces the same way.

150
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:16,913
There's a reason for that too.

151
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:20,125
It's so you can remove it quickly
if something happens.

152
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:25,088
It's not only for your own safety.
It's so you can help the friends you dive with.

153
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:28,258
We did a thorough safety check.

154
00:08:28,425 --> 00:08:30,760
You're not here alone. I'm here too.

155
00:08:31,386 --> 00:08:33,763
You'll be fine, so be tough and go dive.

156
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:35,932
I'll help you, no matter what.

157
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:41,438
All right!

158
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:45,275
-Here I go!
-Yeah.

159
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,500
Huh? I did it!?

160
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,461
It's not tough at all!

161
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:06,004
I did it!

162
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:13,720
So this is...

163
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:15,847
