164
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,517
A new world...

165
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,978
I didn't know about.

166
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:29,360
-Chisa!
-Iori?

167
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,905
I understand what you were trying to say now!

168
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,699
It's amazing to be able to breathe underwater!

169
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:37,494
-And I can't even swim!
-Oh, really...

170
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:41,998
So, this is what it means to experience
a new world!

171
00:09:42,165 --> 00:09:46,377
So, this is how it feels to go to outer space
and experience zero gravity!

172
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:49,255
-Iori, I know. Now go change...
-I wonder if it feels like

173
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:52,634
-you're floating when you really get into diving...
-People

174
00:09:52,801 --> 00:09:55,845
who only choose what they know
will never experience that joy.

175
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:57,222
What do you mean?

176
00:09:57,388 --> 00:10:00,767
-You don't understand?
-I'm talking about this, of course!

177
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:04,312
It's the joy of learning how to do
something you couldn't do before.

178
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,023
Cheers!

179
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:11,152
-That was good!
-It burns.

180
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,154
Have some food with your drinks.

181
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,865
Thanks!

182
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:17,659
That was great, Iori.

183
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,369
You conquered your fear.

184
00:10:19,536 --> 00:10:21,162
I'm still not great in the water.

185
00:10:21,538 --> 00:10:25,166
But you learned how fun it is
to step into a new world!

186
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:27,919
Yeah! Thank you.

187
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,755
No, you don't have to thank us.

188
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:32,924
Right. Now...

189
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:38,429
There's no reason for you
to say no to this new world either!

190
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,140
No!

191
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:47,313
I drank too much again...

192
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,023
Water...

193
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:51,818
What are you doing?

194
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,450
Let's stay in bed a bit longer.

195
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:07,417
Huh? Uh... Huh?

196
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:13,298
This can't be real.

197
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:16,968
Getting drunk and waking up to
someone half-naked sleeping next to me...

198
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,430
Is a normal thing now..

199
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:23,850
I mean... Who is she?

200
00:11:24,017 --> 00:11:27,186
-Oh. This is the first time you guys met.
-Whoa!

201
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:29,272
You know that our club
is an intercollegiate club, right?

202
00:11:29,439 --> 00:11:30,773
INTERCOLLEGIATE CLUB:
A CLUB WITH MEMBERS FROM DIFFERENT COLLEGES

203
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,443
So, she's from another school?

204
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:36,696
She's Azusa Hamaoka from Oumi Women's University.

205
00:11:36,863 --> 00:11:39,282
Why is she sleeping here?

206
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:41,034
Maybe because there was a futon.

207
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,203
I was sleeping in that futon first...

208
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,831
She's not the type of girl to care about that.

209
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:49,959
Whoa.

210
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:53,588
Who would take off their clothes
and sleep in a room with naked guys?

211
00:11:53,922 --> 00:11:55,048
That's what I mean.

212
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:58,259
If you treat her like a girl,
you'll make a fool out of yourself.

213
00:11:59,052 --> 00:12:01,179
You're wearing clothes? That's unusual.

214
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:03,598
We have something to do outside today.

215
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,808
That's why we invited Azusa.

216
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:08,353
-Let's wake her up then.
-Wait.

217
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,606
There's something we have to tell you first.

218
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:14,442
Something important about the Izu Spring Festival.

219
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:22,617
Okay, done!

220
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,954
You're really good.

221
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,372
Not really!

222
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:30,083
We'll be selling okonomiyaki
at the Izu Spring Festival?

223
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:32,710
-It's delicious!
-It has to be!

224
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:35,380
The sales will go to fund our club.

225
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:39,884
Today, we're going to have the freshmen
learn how to make these.

226
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:42,929
What about you, Tokki and Bukki?

227
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:46,516
-Oh, we're...
-Tokita! Kotobuki!

228
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:48,893
-Let's go!
-Okay.

229
00:12:49,686 --> 00:12:51,312
We're going to prep the equipment.

230
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:53,398
When we're done,
we'll eat with everyone.

231
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:55,066
So, make a lot of them.

232
00:12:55,525 --> 00:12:56,693
Okay.

233
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,278
-Then let's begin!
-Okay.

234
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:02,031
Let's do it, Kohei!

235
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:04,033
Leave it to me, Kitahara!

236
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:06,494
Something about the Izu Spring Festival?

237
00:13:06,661 --> 00:13:08,246
It's not about the male pageant?

238
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:10,623
Actually, it is related to that...

239
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,418
We want you to convince Chisa.

240
00:13:13,835 --> 00:13:15,003
What do you mean?

241
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:17,755
There's an Izu Spring Festival
women's beauty pageant.

242
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:21,634
We want Chisa to enter so that
we can get more funds for our club.

243
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:25,179
-You want us to convince her to enter!?
-That's impossible!

244
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:28,141
But if she wins,

245
00:13:28,725 --> 00:13:31,519
you guys don't have to enter
the male pageant anymore.

246
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:35,231
All right! Let's do it!

247
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:43,156
Normally, Chisa would never agree
to enter the women's beauty pageant.

248
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:47,035
Then we just have to put her
in an abnormal condition.

249
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:49,162
We'll get her drunk, she'll loosen up,

250
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:51,205
and we'll get her to enter the pageant!

251
00:13:51,748 --> 00:13:53,833
It's hot today, Kohei!

252
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,209
Right, Kitahara!

253
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,879
It's so hot I'm going to get heatstroke!

254
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:00,548
We have to stay hydrated!

255
00:14:00,715 --> 00:14:03,092
I'll go bring something to drink!

256
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:06,471
VODKA + WHISKEY
OOLONG TEA

257
00:14:06,721 --> 00:14:09,432
-Here's some oolong tea.
-Oh, thanks.

258
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:12,393
Kitahara, got it?
The alcohol is in my right hand.

259
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:15,021
The right hand is for Chisa.
The left hand is for me.

260
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:17,732
Hey, Chisa. Have a drink.

261
00:14:17,899 --> 00:14:19,984
I can't stop right now.
I'll have some later.

262
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:22,570
Then I'll take it.

263
00:14:22,737 --> 00:14:23,863
Huh?

264
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,865
VODKA + WHISKEY

265
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:30,620
-Aren't you going to drink?
-Well...

266
00:14:30,787 --> 00:14:33,790
What? Is there something weird in it?

267
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,294
Of course not!
Come on, drink up, Kitahara!

268
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:40,755
Yeah! You're right!

269
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:43,758
What's wrong, Iori?

270
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:45,635
Oh, nothing.

271
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:47,678
You bastard! Look what you did!

272
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:49,639
It was unavoidable!

273
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,265
Let's switch!

274
00:14:51,516 --> 00:14:53,351
I'll do it this time.

275
00:14:53,518 --> 00:14:55,895
I'll bring some drinks!

276
00:14:58,064 --> 00:14:59,649
What are you making?

277
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,486
Chisa!? This isn't--

278
00:15:03,653 --> 00:15:06,155
You guys sure are pathetic.

279
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:10,243
You're trying to get Imamura to drink that, right?

280
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:15,915
Kohei. Here's some tea.

281
00:15:16,082 --> 00:15:17,834
Oh. Thanks.

282
00:15:21,546 --> 00:15:23,297
Sorry. It was unavoidable.

283
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:26,926
How was this unavoidable!?

284
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:32,557
Good job!

285
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:34,892
I'm not as good as you, though.

286
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:36,227
It's okay!

287
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,437
It's just for the school festival.

288
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:45,820
In a setting like this...

289
00:15:45,987 --> 00:15:47,155
What?

290
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:50,950
-Don't you feel like having a beer?
-I knew you'd say that! So I brought some!

291
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:52,660
I don't want any.

292
00:15:53,995 --> 00:15:55,580
Can I have some?

293
00:15:58,499 --> 00:16:00,334
You two are really considerate!

294
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:01,502
Well, well...

295
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:03,838
We're extremely delighted.

296
00:16:05,423 --> 00:16:08,342
Just like I heard from Nanaka. You're cute.

297
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:11,179
-From Nanaka?
-Are you guys close?

298
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:13,347
We talk on the phone sometimes.

299
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:16,434
That's why I know a lot about you,

300
00:16:16,601 --> 00:16:18,769
-Iori.
-Oh.

301
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,980
She told me lots of things.

302
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:22,982
Nanaka...

303
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:27,236
I have to go call my friend...

304
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:31,949
Iori. That's disgusting.

305
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:34,035
What are you doing?

306
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:38,456
That porn and that gay porn...
It's all a misunderstanding!

307
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:40,082
It's okay!

308
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,668
No, it's not okay...

309
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,213
Actually,

310
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,215
I'm okay with both too.

311
00:16:51,469 --> 00:16:54,555
It's nice to meet someone who's into the same stuff!

312
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:56,807
Let's talk someday, okay?

313
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:59,894
-Into the same stuff?
-She's talking about diving, right?

314
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:02,271
Hey, Kitahara!

315
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:04,899
There's no time for meaningless conversation!

316
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:07,527
This is pretty important...

317
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,030
Is something wrong?

318
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:14,158
-No! Nothing!
-I'm going to get some drinks!

319
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:18,579
